vocabulary.definition: a state of disorder due to the absence or nonrecognition of authority
vocabulary.example: The anarchy in the city led to widespread chaos and confusion.

vocabulary.definition: an expression of good wishes when parting or saying goodbye
vocabulary.example: She bid farewell to her colleagues as she left the company.

vocabulary.definition: an object made by a human being, typically of cultural or historical interest
vocabulary.example: The museum displayed ancient artifacts from the Roman Empire.

vocabulary.definition: to become or make larger or more extensive
vocabulary.example: The company plans to expand its operations to new markets.

vocabulary.definition: repairing or restoring something to good condition
vocabulary.example: She spent hours mending the torn dress to make it wearable again.

vocabulary.definition: a place of refuge or safety
vocabulary.example: The wildlife sanctuary provided a safe haven for endangered species.
